en, die nicht zuletzt der Bewahrung von materiellen und symbolischen Privilegien dient. Weil die Anderen dämonisch und ungezügelt sind, so die vielleicht kürzeste Analyseformel, sind wir befugt, uns vor ihnen und unsere Vorrechte zu schützen.Die Beiträge des Bandes klären diese Verhältnisse rassismuskritisch auf und widersprechen ihnen.  aThe recent media, political and everyday treatment of forced migration has made overt racism "socially acceptable" again. In this way, the discussion of "refugees" and "migrants" following the events in Cologne on New Years' Eve has increasingly taken on the tone of the demonisation of the imagined Other. As this is linked to the "tightening of the asylum act" and a European refugee politics that is increasingly isolationist, this demonisation also preserves material and symbolic relations of privilege. Because the Others are demonic and rampant, as the most concise formation of the analysis goes, we are empowered to protect ourselves from them. It is from this perspective that researchers come forward to speak against the hegemonic discourse.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aMigration, Internal. 0aRacism. 4aDiskriminierung. 4aFlucht. 4aFlüchtlingsforschung. 4aFremdenfeindlichkeit. 4aGruppenbezogene Menschenfeindlichkeit. 4aKulturwissenschaft. 4aMigration. 4aMigrationspolitik. 4aOthering. 4aRassismuskritik. 4aRepräsentation. 4aXenophobie. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Discrimination & Race Relations.2bisacsh  aCultural Studies.  aDiscrimination.  aFleeing.  aMigration Policy.  aMigration.  aOthering.  aRefugee Studies.  aRepresentation.  aXenophobia.1 aAmir-Moazami, Schirin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrumlik, Micha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCastro Varela, María do 